aragraph\" ><strong>Sage, the Forager</strong></p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Auri, the Bard</strong></p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Rin, the Guardian</strong></p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2435450/extras/19bdb64563317895673d7c5779118060.avif?t=1759868843\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2435450/extras_big/19bdb64563317895673d7c5779118060.avif?t=1759868843 width=800 height=280 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2435450/extras/93cadc64433f92123c969007421b1012.webp?t=1759868843\" width=600 height=31 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >The Story</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>A lifetime past</strong>, Farloon's founder saved his people with a stolen book of secrets. Now, with his death, the payment comes due - the souls of your city. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Only <strong>returning the grimoire</strong> to its rightful wardens may divert Farloon's fate - but a deadly desert lies between you and your city's salvation. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>CAN YOU RETURN THE TOME IN TIME? HOW WILL YOU SURVIVE ARID AZOOVE?</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2435450/extras/4f90789c7635f537fa230848f564369d.avif?t=1759868843\" width=600 height=260 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2435450/extras/93cadc64433f92123c969007421b1012.webp?t=1759868843\" width=600 height=31 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Replayability and Progression</strong></h2><